annotationA: Probable dolichol-phosphate mannosyltransferase; Transfers mannose from GDP-mannose to dolichol monophosphate to form dolichol phosphate mannose (Dol-P-Man) which is the mannosyl donor in pathways leading to N-glycosylation, glycosyl phosphatidylinositol membrane anchoring, and O- mannosylation of proteins; Belongs to the glycosyltransferase 2 family
annotationB: RE21160p; Mannose-1-phosphate guanylyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: biosynthetic process
